### Fetch decision logic

```js
async function shouldFetch(seriesId) {
  const cached = getCache(seriesId);

  // No cache — always fetch
  if (!cached) return true;

  const now = Date.now();
  const nextRelease = cached.nextExpectedRelease;

  // New release hasn't happened yet — use cache, show countdown
  if (now < nextRelease) return false;

  // Release window has passed — fetch to see if new data is out
  // (FRED may update slightly after the official time; add 30min buffer)
  if (now > nextRelease + 30 * 60 * 1000) return true;

  // We're in the 30min window — could go either way; use cache
  return false;
}
```

### Countdown display

For each series, show its countdown to next release as part of the status bar. Think of how financial data terminals show "Next: Fed Balance Sheet in 2d 14h 22m".

```
┌─ Data Status ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
│  🟢 Fed Balance Sheet    Apr 10 · Next release: Thu Apr 17 4:30pm ET   │
│  🟢 ECB Balance Sheet    Apr 8  · Next release: Tue Apr 15 10:00am CET │
│  🟡 US M2                Apr 1  · Next release: Tue Apr 22 1:00pm ET   │
│  🟠 Japan BOJ            Mar 20 · Next release: ~Apr 23               │
│  🟠 China M2             Mar 12 · Next release: ~Apr 14               │
│  🟠 Australia M2         Feb 28 · Next release: ~Apr 30  ⚠️ 6wk lag  │
└────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘
```

Status dot colours:
- 🟢 Green — data is current (within expected release window)
- 🟡 Yellow — data is approaching staleness (next release due within 24h)
- 🟠 Amber — monthly series (always somewhat lagged; expected)
- 🔴 Red — data is overdue (past next release time but no new data fetched)

### Auto-fetch on page load

```js
async function initDashboard() {
  const series = ['WALCL', 'M2SL', 'ECBASSETSW', 'JPNASSETS',
                  'MYAGM2CNM189N', 'MYAGM2AUM189N', /* FX rates */];

  // Check each series in parallel
  const fetchPromises = series.map(async (id) => {
    if (await shouldFetch(id)) {
      const data = await fetchFred(id);
      saveCache(id, data);
    }
    return getCache(id).data;
  });

  const allData = await Promise.all(fetchPromises);
  renderDashboard(allData);
  startCountdownTimers(); // Update countdown display every minute
}
```

### Manual refresh

A "Refresh Now" button bypasses the schedule check and forces a re-fetch of all series. It should show a spinner and re-render on completion. Include a soft warning: "Fetching early — new data may not be available yet."

