### 8.4 FRED API Call Template
```js
async function fetchFred(seriesId, apiKey) {
  const url = new URL('https://api.stlouisfed.org/fred/series/observations');
  url.searchParams.set('series_id', seriesId);
  url.searchParams.set('api_key', apiKey);
  url.searchParams.set('file_type', 'json');
  url.searchParams.set('observation_start', '2010-01-01');
  url.searchParams.set('units', 'lin'); // raw values
  const res = await fetch(url);
  const json = await res.json();
  return json.observations; // [{ date, value }, ...]
}
```

### 8.5 Missing / "." Values
FRED sometimes returns `"."` for missing values. Filter these out:
```js
const clean = observations.filter(o => o.value !== '.');
```

### 8.6 Tooltip Formatting
- Liquidity values: format as `$X.XX T` (trillions) or `$X,XXX B` (billions)
- BTC: format as `$XX,XXX`
- S&P / NDQ: format as `X,XXX`
